<title>CZECH REPUBLIC: Shares in Czech Skoda rise on U.S. order.</title>
<headline>Shares in Czech Skoda rise on U.S. order.</headline>
<dateline>PRAGUE 1997-04-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares in the Czech Republic's biggest engineering company Skoda Plzen a.s. surged on Tuesday after the company said it had won an order to supply trolley buses worth $170 million to the U.S. city of San Francisco.</p>
<p>Towards the end of continuous trading on the Prague Stock Exchange on Tuesday, Skoda shares had risen 39 crowns, 4.6 percent, to 885.  </p>
<p>The order is the largest supply of Czech goods ever to the United States.</p>
<p>Skoda Plzen is in no way related to the car maker Skoda Auto.</p>
<p>-- Robin Shepherd, Prague Newsroom, 420-2-2423-0003</p>
